snippet.textDisplay:
Theory before actually watching the video: the cold not affecting her physical body is referring to her being impervious to the effects cold has on her body - aka the traditional issues humans face of hypothermia, heart failure, and cell damage as a result of overly cold temperatures. She doesn't experience that effect because it's a biological effect that her magic protects her from.
This does not, however, mean she can't BE frozen. At the right temperature EVERYTHING freezes
The "cold not bothering her" does, however, explain how she can UNFREEZE afterwards without being completely dead (see the Mr Freeze theory on film theory from ages ago for explanation as to why she should BE dead https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=2nc9AFcKIuM.)


This does not explain Anna unfreezing in the first movie, but I'll leave that to better theorists than I.

snippet.textDisplay:
I’ve got 2 theories on why she could freeze:
Theory 1: You could just say the fact that she is already confirmed in the movie to be an ice spirit, along with the ability to have some control over water (so she is part water, part ice(?)), and has water on her, means that when she landed it that part of the cave, which happens to be really cold, along with her ice spirit, she could’ve just finally reached the temperature to freeze, without any sort of impact to trigger it. I say this because many other parts of both frozen 1 and 2 would have strong enough impacts to freeze anyway.

Theory 2: Along with all the water covering her and ice spirit stuff, near the start she mention everyday her powers get stronger, and so what if now that she has arrived to what seems to be her power source, it get so strong that it does anaphylaxis (body self defence is to choke itself), and to protect herself from whatever danger is about to come, her power becomes strong enough to cover herself in ice. This would explain why she is so shocked and can’t control her power, as it is a self defence feature.

But like hey, this is just some theories. Some FILM theories.

snippet.textDisplay:
I love your theories but 1: in my personal opinion this was better than the first, music wise and plot wise and wasn’t confusing at all
2: I think the reason she froze to death was a two part explanation to fully explain. The first part is the song that plays a bunch, the one lullaby their mom sung them. It doesn’t specifically say “oh you’re going to freeze to death” but it’s basically a metaphor. “In her waters, deep and true. Lay the answers and a path for you. Dive down deep into her sound. But not too far or you’ll be drowned” for her and since it’s a glacier the “drowning” is just really freezing. And the second part is think of it this way, her powers were given to her by the spirits of nature to be the bridge between the two worlds to bring them together. Bring harmony and that’s also why there’s both her and Anna, you can’t have a bridge with only one side cause then that bridge wouldn’t work but that’s not the point of this part. The point is think of her and the spirit of nature being parent/child, there’s powers for example the parent is going to be stronger with it since they have more practice with it. Which is how I thought of it when I was watching it, the spirits of nature is the parent and is stronger which is why she could be frozen. That’s how I saw it though 🤷🏻‍♀️

It's really REALLY annoying, it's not what we click on your videos for and chances are that people who click on Frozen Theories... you know... like Frozen? It's fine if you are not one of them but then... don't make that video, maybe? But then I guess you couldn't capitalize on the powerfull franchise other people actually made - you know, the same people you accuse of being greedy. And speaking of hypocrisy: critisizing others for merchandisable costumes rings a bit hollow when you regularly interrupt your videos for shameless merch plugs. So you are really not one to talk, buddy.
Maybe shitting on Disney is what the cool and edgy kids do nowadays but it's really annoying to keep hearing this again and again and again and again - especially in videos that are not supposed to be reviews!

I feel like you are falling a bit from grace here recently. The salt in your videos is really getting excessive. Turn it down a bit, maybe. That would be great.

snippet.textDisplay:
The point of Frozen II is that Elsa is the fifth element and a link between worlds (sorry it had to be), the forest and Arendelle! Ahtohallan is frozen because of the war (something psychologically: water has memory - no one remembers the forest - the memory is frozen - the water is frozen) and Elsa has her powers by Ahtohallan, so she has ice powers.
Now she walks through Ahtohallan and sees the water remembering everything and as she sees her grandpa beeing the villain, she sees that she can't do anything, she thinks she failed, Ahtohallan made a mistake by giving her powers and so her fear to fail (she has her whole life) makes her freeze.
That's my theory!

snippet.textDisplay: I actually think it makes sense for her to freeze. Throughout the movie she's constantly warned (through the song her mother sang about the magical river, by Anna, and she herself knows she shouldn't go too far) but she does anyway and alone, as we see how she distances herself from her loved ones even after her promise to share anything that bothers her. Nonetheless, Disney wants to show that family is an extremely important step to discovering who you truly are. The ice queen FREEZING just stresses enough how you shouldn't distance yourself from the ones you love. After all in the first movie, the family love and trust saved Anna after Elsa realized that she doesn't necessarily have to be alone and deal with her problems alone when there are people who love and believe in her. And in frozen 2, she goes against her promise (again controversial) BUT to protect the people she loves out of fear (fear is her greatest enemy as we know from frozen 1) of loosing them to the dangers of this adventure. But that's the wrong choice, no matter the danger people that love you will stick with you till the end, and I believe that the isolation Elsa put herself in in order to discover her true identity is shown through her freezing. But hey that's just a theory! ❤ btw absolutely love your channel!
